FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40705
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,FMeanwhile, Apple announced a global
OL,7,Fchange to its security settings that
OL,8,Fwould allow stolen phones to be locked
OL,9,Fup. In a recent update, the tech firm
OL,10,Fmade "stolen device protection" a
OL,11,Fdefault setting for all users. The
OL,12,Fchange makes devices reported as
OL,13,Fmissing significantly harder to
OL,14,Faccess, reset and resell.
OL,16,FThe Met has some of the highest rates
OL,17,Fper thousand people of personal
OL,18,Frobbery and theft from the person in
OL,19,FEngland and Wales, among which phones
OL,20,Fare a "significant" problem.
OL,26,@rD@FOUrD@_O]|D@GOU|D@SO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
