OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40707
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,FIn the UK, the Met has seen adverts on
OL,7,FSnapchat offering children as much as
OL,8,F#380 to steal a single iPhone, with a
OL,9,Fbonus of #100 for stealing 10.
OL,11,FSir Mark Rowley said: "I gave an
OL,12,Fultimatum to tech firms ` take urgent
OL,13,Fsteps to prevent stolen phones from
OL,14,Fbeing resold and reused, or we will
OL,15,Fcall on Government to step in and
OL,16,Flegislate.
OL,26,@sD@WOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40708
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,F"For the first time, we are routinely
OL,7,Fsharing intelligence on stolen
OL,8,Fdevices, building a joint picture of
OL,9,Fhow these phones move and whether they
OL,10,Freappear in circulation.
OL,12,F"That partnership is already making a
OL,13,Fdifference.
OL,15,F"If stolen phones cannot be
OL,16,Freactivated, their value collapses,
OL,17,Fand so does the incentive to steal
OL,18,Fthem.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G8/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40709
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,F"We are driving up the risk for
OL,7,Foffenders while cutting off the
OL,8,Freward."
OL,10,FThe Met has written to the Home
OL,11,FSecretary asking for legislation to
OL,12,Fmake phone companies publish data on
OL,13,Fstolen devices and whether they are
OL,14,Freconnected, and to enforce measures
OL,15,Fto make stolen devices unusable.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@HO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,FIt said that in the 12 months from
OL,7,FJune 2025 to May 2026 the number of
OL,8,Fthefts and robberies where phones were
OL,9,Fstolen fell by 14,000, a reduction of
OL,10,F18% on the previous year, and that the
OL,11,Ffirst five months of this year saw
OL,12,F6,700 fewer, a drop of 20.6%.
OL,14,FWestminster, where between 69% and 72%
OL,15,Fof thefts from the person and personal
OL,16,Frobberies each week involve phones,
OL,17,Fhas seen a reduction of 45.8% so far
OL,18,Fthis calendar year.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,FAt a conference on phone theft in
OL,7,FMarch, the Met called for anti-theft
OL,8,Fprotection to be switched on by
OL,9,Fdefault, stolen phones to be rendered
OL,10,Funusable, and better access to IMEI
OL,11,F(International Mobile Equipment
OL,12,FIdentity) data to make it easier to
OL,13,Freturn devices to their owners.
OL,15,FFigures released under Freedom of
OL,16,FInformation legislation show only a
OL,17,Ffraction of devices taken in London
OL,18,Fare returned to their owners.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/12
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1781348571
OL,3,CPolice push for phone companies to be
OL,4,Cforced to make stolen handsets unusable
OL,6,FBetween 2017 and February 27 2024, a
OL,7,Ftotal 587,498 phones were stolen in
OL,8,FLondon excluding the City, 13,998 of
OL,9,Fwhich were recovered, and 573,500 were
OL,10,Fnot.
OL,12,FThe force also solves one of the
OL,13,Fsmallest proportion of these offences
OL,14,Fcompared with others in England and
OL,15,FWales.
OL,17,FIn the year to the end of December
OL,18,F2025, 6.9% of personal robbery cases
OL,19,Fended with a suspect being identified
OL,20,Fand dealt with, while the rate was
OL,21,F0.9% for theft from the person.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/12
